with equality if and only if formula_25 is equal to a constant a.e.; the path should be travelled at constant speed. It happens that minimizers of formula_26 also minimize formula_27, because they turn out to be affinely parameterized, and the inequality is an equality. The usefulness of this approach is that the problem of seeking minimizers of formula_17 is a more robust variational problem. Indeed, formula_26 is a &quot;convex function&quot; of formula_30, so that within each isotopy class of &quot;reasonable functions&quot;, one ought to expect existence, uniqueness, and regularity of minimizers. In contrast, &quot;minimizers&quot; of the functional formula_27 are generally not very regular, because arbitrary reparameterizations are allowed.

The Euler–Lagrange equations of motion for the functional formula_17 are then given in local coordinates by
